{
  "texts": [
    "These faults could jeopardize human safety by unintentional contact with an energized exposed conductor.",
    "Hence it is an important but difficult task to detect these types of faults.",
    "Therefore, there are specially designed algorithms for HIF detection.",
    "In HIF detection, after feature extraction from the measurements a boundary should be found to separate a faulty state from healthy ones.",
    "Among different classification methods ML-based methods have higher accuracy in pattern classification, fast response, noise removal ability and prediction capability (Hotelling, 1933)."
  ]
}